<!-- ================= NOTES ================= -->

<div class="section">
<h2>📊 Maths – Percentages & Ratio</h2>

<p>
Percent means “out of 100”.
Example:
50% = 50/100 = 0.5
</p>

<p>
Ratio compares quantities.
Example:
2:3 means 2 parts to 3 parts.
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>📖 English – Comprehension & Writing</h2>

<p>
Learners must:
• Understand deeper meaning  
• Identify themes  
• Write structured paragraphs  
</p>

<p>
Focus:
• Clear ideas  
• Good vocabulary  
• Correct grammar  
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>🔬 NST – Systems in the Body</h2>

<p>
Human body systems:
• Digestive system  
• Circulatory system  
• Respiratory system  
</p>

<p>
Each system works together to keep the body alive.
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>🌍 Geography – Resources & Trade</h2>

<p>
Resources:
• Natural (water, minerals)  
• Human (skills, labour)  
</p>

<p>
Trade = exchange of goods between places.
</p>
</div>

<!-- ================= COMPREHENSION ================= -->

<div class="section">
<h2>📖 Comprehension</h2>

<p>
A group of learners visited a farm to learn about resources. They saw how water was used to grow crops 
and how workers helped harvest food. The teacher explained that both natural and human resources are important. 
The learners realised that everything they use comes from resources and must be used wisely.
</p>

